        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 4:29PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 429 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Tilton, or near Dalton,
moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dalton, Chatsworth, Resaca, Carters, Tails Creek, Ramhurst, Oakman,
Fort Mountain State Park, Tilton, Nickelsville, North Georgia
Speedway, and Audubon.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
